theorems.statement:
Two immediate consequences of Szele's criterion will be used repeatedly:
(i) $2$ is the only even cyclic integer (if $n$ is even and $n>2$, then $2\mid n$ and $2\mid \varphi(n)$, so $\gcd(n,\varphi(n))\ge2$);
(ii) $1$ is the only square in $C$ (if $n$ is a square $>1$, then $p\mid n$ and $p\mid \varphi(n)$ for some prime $p$, so again $\gcd(n,\varphi(n))>1$). All odd primes are cyclic since $\gcd(p,\varphi(p))=\gcd(p,p-1)=1$.

